## Your Task

1. Check via MCP whether a PR already exists for branch `{{.Branch}}` targeting `{{.BaseBranch}}`. If one already exists, report its URL and stop.

2. Generate a PR title and description using the following format:

   ```
   ## Summary
   <2–4 bullet points summarising what was implemented, referencing the ticket>

   ## Changes
   <grouped by area — e.g. CLI, config, template — with file-level callouts for significant changes>

   ## Testing
   <what was tested; links to relevant test files>

   ## Review notes
   <anything reviewers should pay attention to; flags from code/security review if present>

   ## Ticket link
   <link to the original ticket if available in context>
   ```

3. Create the PR via MCP targeting `{{.BaseBranch}}`{{if .DraftPR}} as a draft{{end}}.

4. After the PR is created, write the PR URL to:

   `{{.BranchDir}}/context/pr-url.txt`
